  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Today I learned that go test has _both_ `-p` which is how many packages to test in parallel, and `-parallel` which is how many tests per package to run in parallel.  So, the total number of simultaneous postgres connections could be as high as their product.  GitHub runner is 2 vCPU, so that could be 4 or 16 with neither option set (depending on whether hyperthreading shows up for vCPUs), which doesn't seem crazy.",
    "created_at": "2022-06-15T18:34:53Z",
